  "text": "−/− mice were generated in 129/SvJ as previously described [CITATION_1] and backcrossed to C57BL/6J for >10 generations. Microsatellite genotyping showed that DPPI −/− mice were 99.2% congenic with C57BL/6J mice (The Jackson Laboratory). WT C57BL/6J mice were obtained from The Jackson Laboratory. WT and DPPI −/− mice were kept in pathogen-free environment until the time of Sev infection. All animal experiments were performed in compliance with federal laws and in strict accordance with the guidelines established by the Division of Comparative Medicine at Washington University in St. Louis.",
